    <string name="guide_title">On-chain exchange — what to do</string>
    <string name="guide_body">An on-chain BTC-e exchange is only settled once a blockchain node has ordered and verified your transfer. To be able to exchange:\n\n1. Configure a node — set rpc_url (and chain_id) in evolia_chain_config.json inside evolIA\'s home folder.\n\n2. Fund your address with gas — send a little native coin to the address below so your transactions can pay gas.\n\n3. Start evolIA — it deploys the contract once and anchors your proven value as your transferable on-chain balance.\n\n4. Then Transfer to another owner\'s address. Receiving is automatic: your balance grows when a peer pays your address.\n\nWithout a reachable node a transfer stays LOCAL (not settled).</string>
    <string name="guide_address_label">Your funding address (gas):</string>
    <string name="guide_address_pending">(appears after the first on-chain activity)</string>

